      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "There is a growing consensus among urban planners that congestion pricing is a necessary tool for achieving ambitious climate goals in major metropolitan areas. By directly discouraging single-occupancy vehicle use in congested zones, these systems incentivize the adoption of public transit and active mobility. While some argue it's just one solution, most experts view it as a crucial, market-based intervention that complements other sustainability efforts.",
      "source": "target",
